name: Kepler-419
scenarioDescription:
The Kepler-419 Exoplanetary System


Overview

Kepler-419 is a star with 1.39 times the mass of the Sun, and 1.74 times its radius. It is located 3396.30 light years away from the solar system.

Kepler-419 is known to have 2 exoplanets in orbit around it.


Exoplanets in the Kepler-419 system


Kepler-419 b

Kepler-419 b was discovered by the Kepler observatory using the transit method. Its semi-major axis is 0.37 astronomical units, as compared to Earth's which is 1 astronomical unit. The mass of Kepler-419 b is 795 times the mass of Earth. The radius of Kepler-419 b is 10.8 that of Earth. At more than 50 Earth masses, Kepler-419 b is a gas giant, a planet whose mass is mostly made up of hydrogen and helium, like Jupiter and Saturn in our solar system.


Kepler-419 c

Kepler-419 c was discovered by the Kepler observatory using the transit timing variations method. Its semi-major axis is 1.68 astronomical units, as compared to Earth's which is 1 astronomical unit. The mass of Kepler-419 c is 2321.4 times the mass of Earth. At more than 50 Earth masses, Kepler-419 c is a gas giant, a planet whose mass is mostly made up of hydrogen and helium, like Jupiter and Saturn in our solar system.
description: 3D visualisation and gravity simulation of the exoplanet system Kepler-419, which contains 2 planets and was discovered by Kepler.
